There's no logging of who accesses what, making incident response impossible.

```js
const morgan = require('morgan');
app.use(morgan('combined')); // logs IP, method, path, status, user-agent
```

#### 10. No HTTPS Enforcement

The server listens on plain HTTP. In production, enforce TLS.

```js
// If behind a reverse proxy (recommended):
app.set('trust proxy', 1);
// helmet's HSTS header will handle the rest
```

